PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	10010.000	10019.900				Central Committee for Comprehensive Management of Public Security: In 2006, Our Country's Public Security Continues to be Stable	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	20010.000	20019.900				January 16, 2007 19:36	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	30010.000	30019.900				Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, January 16 - (Reporter Li Weiwei) In 2006, which had just ended, our country had comprehensively undertaken safety construction efforts, and further improved the mechanism for investigating and settling of contradictions and dissentions. Our country had also relentlessly carried out the strike-hard campaign, made great efforts in promoting the construction of a social security preventive and control system, and effectively strengthened the construction of grassroots infrastructure. All these had in turn ensured the continued stability of overall public security.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	40010.000	40019.900				According to the 2007 first plenary meeting convened on the 16th by the Central Committee for Comprehensive Management of Public Security, since China started conducting the special campaign for fighting triads and eliminating crime in 2006, public security organs nationwide have investigated and handled 346 cases involving triads. Among them, 296 cases involving mafia-style organizations were transferred for prosecution, 167 cases were prosecuted by procuratorial organs for the crimes of mafia-style organization, while 61 cases have been sentenced by the courts for the crimes of mafia-style organization. In addition, 1,347 evil force groups have also been eliminated.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	40020.000	40029.900				After a large number of mafia-style organizations and evil forces were eliminated, public security and order in many places have been evidently improved, and the sense of security on the part of the public had also been strengthened.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	50010.000	50019.900				At the same time, in 2006, judicial and public security organs nationwide had also insisted on the "strike hard" policy, and had severely, according to the law, cracked down on serious violent crimes such as murders and bombings. This meant that the rising trend of criminal cases had fundamentally been restrained.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	50020.000	50029.900				Statistics indicated that from January to November 2006, the number of criminal cases placed on file by public security organs nationwide stood at 4.185 million, a decline of 0.8% year over year; the number of various criminal cases uncovered rose to 1.947 million, a 4.3% increase year over year; the number of eight types of serious criminal cases placed on file stood at 484,000, a 4.3% decrease year over year; these eight types include arson, explosion, hijack, murder, injury, rape, kidnapping and robbery.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	50030.000	50039.900				Regions like Liaoning, Heilongjiang, and so on have continued to pointedly undertake the special management of murder cases, further maintained the excellent situation with a continuous decline in murder cases, and brought about the improvement of the overall security situation.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	50040.000	50049.900				Public security organs have also arranged and carried out concentrated regulations on explosive materials, firearms, and ammunitions, as well as the work of controlling knives and other tools. They have regulated and eliminated a large number of safety hazards involving explosives, firearms and knives, and prevented and controlled serious violent crimes such as bombings and murders.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	50050.000	50059.900				Regions such as Guangdong and Hunan had conducted posted regulations in counties and cities with serious "Mark Six" gambling, while Yunnan, Guizhou, Hainan and so on had undertaken great efforts to carry out a people's war against drugs, and have also severely cracked down on drug production and drug trafficking activities. They have also undertaken the mandatory detention of drug addicts so as to arrest the rising trend of drug-related criminal cases.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	60010.000	60019.900				In addition, every region has persisted in undertaking rolling investigations, regulating areas with disorderly public security, and solving prominent problems relating to public security.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	60020.000	60029.900				Regions in Jiangxi province had persisted in combining regular investigation and regulation with concentrated investigation and regulation, as well as combined conventional investigation and regulation, with special investigation and regulation. They have also strengthened their efforts in regulating areas with disorderly public security and prominent public security problems.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	60030.000	60039.900				The city of Shanghai has established social security patrol groups comprising of citizens, so as to involve the masses in strengthening investigations into complex public security areas such as key areas, road sections, entertainment and service outlets, trade markets, and so on. This will allow the timely discovery of prominent public security problems, and help organize the relevant authorities in jointly undertaking focal regulation.	0	0	0		
PDA_CMN_20070116.0045	0	60040.000	60049.900				At the beginning of each year, the city of Beijing will investigate and designate 50 areas with a high occurrence of criminal cases, and publish their names in the media. Through dual-way posted supervision from Party leaders and the public security organs of these areas, key regulations are conducted so as to alter the public security situation within a stipulated period.	0	0	0		
